    "recap_headline": "Charlotte",
    "recap_text": "WICHITA, Kan. \u2013\nCharlotte Baseball fell in the rubber match of its series against Wichita State, dropping Sunday's (March 22) contest, 7-2.\nCharlotte (15-9, 1-2 American) was held to seven hits in the game while Wichita State (17-9, 2-1 American) collected 10.\nDylan Koontz\nand\nCale Stricklin\nboth had multi-hit games for the second game in a row against the Shockers, finishing the finale with two knocks apiecde.\nTodd Hudson\n,\nRobert Nedry\n, and\nAdrian Jimenez\nhad the other three hits for the 49ers. Koontz had Charlotte's only extra-base hit of the game, bouncing a ground-rule double over the wall in right.\nChayse Oxborrow\ngot the start on the mound and was saddled with the loss after striking out four batters while allowing three runs in the first 5.1 innings.\nChase Carson\nfollowed for the next 1.1 frames while\nAdam Stanton\n,\nSebastian Perez\n, and\nRyan Combs\ncombined to finish off the final four outs.\nHOW IT HAPPENED\nBoth teams scored in the third inning, with Charlotte striking first on a wild pitch. Stricklin singled to start the frame but was out at second when\nSpencer Nolan\nreached on a fielder's choice. Hudson singled on a hit-and-run executed to perfection that put runners on the corners when Nolan made it to third.\nCody Gunderson\nwas hit by a pitch to load the bases, setting up the wild pitch to bring Nolan home the final 90 feet.\nWichita State leveled the score in the home half, bringing home a run on a fielder's choice. A lead-off walk was followed by a pair of bunt singles to load up the bases, allowing a run to score on a grounder to short when the relay throw to turn a double play wasn't in time.\nThe Shockers took the lead in the next frame, plating two runs from a trio of hits. Another lead-off walk followed by a double put a pair in scoring position and a groundout brought the first run home before a single scored the second run to make it 3-1.\nCharlotte struggled to get runners on in the middle innings, with only Koontz doubling over the wall in the sixth and Jimenez working a walk in the seventh. Both made it to scoring position but the Niners couldn't bring either around to cut into the deficit. Koontz legged out an infield single in the top of the eighth for his second hit of the game, but he didn't make it past first base.\nWichita threatened in the seventh, loading the bases with two outs after a pair of Niner errors, but Stanton came in out of the bullpen and needed only two pitches to get the final out of the frame.\nThe Shockers had multiple runners on again in the eighth, plating four more insurance runs to pull away from the Green and White.\nCharlotte got one of the runs back in the ninth after a Wichita State error extended the inning.\nJohnny Sutryk\nreached on the error with two outs and then came home on a single from Stricklin after the left fielder misplayed the ball for a second error in as many CLT batters.\nUP NEXT\nThe Niners are back at home this week on Tuesday (March 24) with a midweek game against Queens. First pitch between the two Charlotte programs is scheduled for 6 p.m. from Hayes Stadium.",
